Sure! To write an if/then statement in C programming language, you can use the following syntax:

if (condition) {
    // code to execute if the condition is true
} else {
    // code to execute if the condition is false
}

For example, let's say you want to check if a variable named "age" is greater than 18. You can write the following code:

if (age > 18) {
    printf("You are eligible to vote.\n");
} else {
    printf("You are not eligible to vote.\n");
}

This code will print "You are eligible to vote." if the age variable is greater than 18, and "You are not eligible to vote." if the age variable is less than or equal to 18.
